Özdemir wants to preserve jazz education in Stuttgart
In the ongoing discussions about the future of the music academies in Baden-Württemberg has now also Cem Özdemir, national chair of the Greens, turned on.
"I think it is wrong to abandon the" holistic training at the Musikhochschule Stuttgart, Özdemir said the "Stuttgarter Nachrichten."
Jazz and classical music belong together at the Jazz location in Stuttgart.
This contradicts Özdemir, in Stuttgart as a favorite for a direct mandate in the federal election on 22 September, the green-red state government.
These forces on the basis of an expert study an overhaul of five music academies in Baden-Württemberg.
After that, among other things, the course of jazz and pop should be shifted from the Mannheim Musikhochschule Stuttgart at the Conservatory.
